title: Independent Candidate Muhammad Naeem wins PP-263 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Independent Candidate, Muhammad Naeem has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-263, Rahim Yar Khan-IX by securing 61,401 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Rana Mahmood-ul-Hassan of Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) who bagged 46,220 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 52.91%.
